LOAD DATA

local <- read.csv(paste0(dataDir, "/assignment_all_NCBI_local.csv"))
local$ncbi_local <- paste0("ncbi_local")

ncbi <- read.csv(paste0(dataDir, "/assignment_all_NCBI.csv"))
ncbi$ncbi_local <- paste0("ncbi")

data <- rbind(local, ncbi)


data <- data %>%
    separate_wider_delim(cols = database, delim = "_",
        names = c("DB", "Derep", "GeoRestricted",
            "PrimerTrimmed"), cols_remove = FALSE)

data$taxlevelf = factor(data$taxlevel, levels = c("Kingdom",
    "Phylum", "Class", "Order", "Family", "Genus",
    "Species"))

data$db_label <- paste(data$Derep, data$PrimerTrimmed,
    sep = "_")

PLOT

db_theme <- theme_set(theme_bw(base_size = 11)) +
    theme(panel.border = element_blank(), panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), panel.background = element_blank(),
        axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90,
            vjust = 1, hjust = 1, colour = "black",
            size = 14), axis.text.y = element_text(size = 14),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 15),
        strip.text = element_text(colour = "black",
            face = "bold", size = 12), strip.background = element_rect(colour = "black",
            fill = "white"))

(p_1 <- data %>%
    filter(taxlevel == "Order" & ncbi_local ==
        "ncbi_local") %>%
    ggplot(aes(y = fractionReadsAssigned, x = factor(DB,
        levels = c("DB1", "DB2", "DB3", "DB4",
            "DB5", "DB6", "DB7", "DB8")))) + geom_boxplot(color = "black",
    outlier.shape = NA) + geom_point(size = 1,
    color = "grey50") + stat_summary(fun = mean,
    geom = "point", shape = 22, size = 2.5, color = "grey30",
    fill = "red") + scale_x_discrete(labels = NULL) +
    xlab("") + ylab("Order") + facet_grid(. ~
    factor(GeoRestricted, levels = c("NotGeoRestricted",
        "GeoRestricted"), labels = c("No Geographic Restriction",
        "Geographic Restriction")), scales = "free_x",
    space = "free_x") + db_theme)

(p_2 <- data %>%
    filter(taxlevel == "Order" & ncbi_local ==
        "ncbi") %>%
    ggplot(aes(y = fractionReadsAssigned, x = factor(DB,
        levels = c("DB9", "DB10", "DB11", "DB12",
            "DB13", "DB14", "DB15", "DB16")))) +

    fill = "red") + scale_x_discrete(labels = NULL) +
    xlab("") + ylab("") + facet_grid(. ~ factor(GeoRestricted,
    levels = c("NotGeoRestricted", "GeoRestricted"),
    labels = c("No Geographic Restriction", "Geographic Restriction")),
    scales = "free_x", space = "free_x") + db_theme)

grid.newpage()
pushViewport(viewport(layout = grid.layout(50,
    12)))
vplayout <- function(x, y) viewport(layout.pos.row = x,
    layout.pos.col = y)

print(p_1 + ggtitle("a.") + theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 20,
    hjust = -0.06, vjust = 1, face = "bold", family = "Helvetica")),
    vp = vplayout(1:11, 1:6))

print(p_2 + ggtitle("b.") + theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 20,
    hjust = -0.06, vjust = 1, face = "bold", family = "Helvetica")),
    vp = vplayout(1:11, 7:12))


# Get the ggplot grob
p_3_gt <- ggplotGrob(p_3)

# Locate the tops of the plot panels
panels <- grep("panel", p_3_gt$layout$name)
top <- unique(p_3_gt$layout$t[panels])

# Remove the rows immediately above the plot
# panel
p_3_gt = p_3_gt[-(top - 1), ]
p_3_gt$vp = viewport(layout.pos.row = 13:21, layout.pos.col = 1:6)
grid.draw(p_3_gt)
